results.name: Irregular triangle read by rows where T(H(u),H(v)) is the coefficient of m(v) in p(u), where H is Heinz number, m is monomial symmetric functions, and p is power sum symmetric functions.
comment: The Heinz number of an integer partition (y_1, ..., y_k) is prime(y_1) * ... * prime(y_k).
example: For example, row 18 gives: p(221) = m(5) + 2m(32) + m(41) + 2m(221).
results.author: _Gus Wiseman_, Nov 20 2018
